title.narrative: 5.2 Improved accessibility and quality of care and pre-primary education for young boys and girls in target districts, by the end of December 2019, with a focus on vulnerable groups.

description.narrative: Significant progress was made towards improved access and quality of pre-primary education with the finalization of the National Early Childhood Development (ECD) policy for Cabinet approval. Provisions of the policy, Early Childhood Care Education curriculum and minimum standards were included in the “Learning Through Play” curriculum to strengthen quality implementation. This was improved through training of 1,560 ECD educators and facilitators in play-based early learning. A total of 3,605 children (51 per cent girls) enrolled in community-based ECD centers and 88,855 children (54 percent girls) received appropriate teaching, learning and play resources reaching) in 1,225 centers (97 per cent formal). | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2019
